The petroleum activities disturb feeding cause abandonment of maternity dens and disrupt polar bear life cycles.
Polar bears depend on sea ice for their main prey -- ringed seals and bearded seals.
More pregnant polar bears in Alaska are digging snow dens on land of sea ice.
The hunting of bear cubs and pregnant bears is banned.
Polar bears are not the only species threatened.
Polar bears depend on sea ice so they can travel and float to hunt seal and to reach coastal areas off Greenland Canada Alaska Russia and Scandinavia.

